Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Distributed Memory Management Module

Provides distributed memory management, node coordination, and load balancing for large-scale systems.

Features:
- Distributed memory manager and node coordination
- Load balancing and distributed allocation APIs
- Global pointer management
- Integration with allocators and GC
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note

Note: Distributed Memory Types and Interfaces
Type DistributedMemoryManager is Dictionary with:
    nodes as List[MemoryNode]
    coordinator as MemoryCoordinator
    load_balancer as MemoryLoadBalancer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MemoryNode is Dictionary with:
    id as String
    address as String
    available_memory as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MemoryCoordinator is Dictionary with:
    register_node as Function that takes node as MemoryNode returns None
    unregister_node as Function that takes node_id as String returns None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MemoryLoadBalancer is Dictionary with:
    select_node as Function that takes size as Integer returns MemoryNode
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DistributedPointer is Dictionary with:
    node_id as String
    local_address as Integer
    size as Integer
    global_handle as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "distribute_allocation" that takes manager as DistributedMemoryManager and size as Integer returns DistributedPointer:
    Let best_node be manager.load_balancer.select_node(size)
    Let local_pointer be allocate_on_node(best_node, size)
    Return DistributedPointer with:
        node_id as best_node.id
        local_address as local_pointer.address
        size as size
        global_handle as register_distributed_allocation(manager.coordinator, local_pointer)
        metadata as dictionary containing 